=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ezu1665702793711.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ezu1665702793711.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ezu1665702793711.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ezu1665702793711\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define Relationships Worksheet\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use this worksheet to define the relationships of the current entity, which must have the Many role in a one-to-many relationship.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__p_d5417e1_d5418e1_d5419e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eei1704363244858.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eei1704363244858.html\" title=\"A relationship is an association between one entity and another. It is modeled as a development object belonging to the many-side entity in a one-to-many relationship.\">Relationships</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__section_fgx_2f2_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216856e61\">Tools</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__ul_ofq_ff2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__li_d2519e1_d2520e1_d2521e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Resource Browser: Model</span>—find and\n          select the One entity for a relationship. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__li_d2522e1_d2523e1_d2524e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Relationship Editor</span>—graphical\n          editor for defining the relationships and foreign keys in the current entity. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__section_inx_ff2_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216856e80\">How To </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__ul_hm2_hf2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__li_d2525e1_d2526e1_d2527e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hpk1704364153312.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hpk1704364153312.html\" title=\"Each modeled entity can have zero or more relationships with other modeled entities. These are used to enforce data integrity when creating and deleting data.\">Define Relationships Between Modeled Entities</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__ul_jm2_hf2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__li_d2528e1_d2529e1_d2530e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qle1665702773192.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qle1665702773192.html\" title=\"Use the Uniface IDE to develop an application, following the Uniface development paradigm of Model, Construct, Build, and Deploy.\">Using the Uniface IDE</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ezu1665702793711__li_d2531e1_d2532e1_d2533e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkp1665702773261.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkp1665702773261.html\" title=\"Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same.\">Working with Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eei1704363244858.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Relationships</a><p>A relationship is an association between one entity and another. It is modeled as a development object belonging to the many-side entity in a one-to-many relationship.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nbo1665702702246.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Delete Constraint</a><p>Defines Uniface behavior when an occurrence of the One Entity is deleted, and there are related occurrences of the many entity available in the component data structure. Valid values are Restricted (default), Cascading, or Nullify.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fnf1665702703926.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Referential Integrity</a><p>Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527407\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527407\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Relationships Worksheet Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Relationships Worksheet Use this worksheet to define the relationships of the current entity, which must have the Many role in a one-to-many relationship. For more information, see Relationships . Tools Resource Browser: Model —find and select the One entity for a relationship. Relationship Editor —graphical editor for defining the relationships and foreign keys in the current entity. How To Define Relationships Between Modeled Entities Using the Uniface IDE Working with Development Objects Related Links Relationships A relationship is an association between one entity and another. It is modeled as a development object belonging to the many-side entity in a one-to-many relationship. Delete Constraint Defines Uniface behavior when an occurrence of the One Entity is deleted, and there are related occurrences of the many entity available in the component data structure. Valid values are Restricted (default), Cascading, or Nullify. Referential Integrity Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}